## What I Am Still Thinking About

Something I am genuinely wrestling with: how do you build a culture where people treat security as an ongoing discipline rather than a periodic compliance exercise?

The compliance mindset is understandable. Audits have deadlines. Certifications have expiry dates. It is natural to focus energy around those external pressure points. But that rhythm creates exactly the gap that attackers exploit — the period between audits when attention drifts.

I do not have a complete answer yet, but I think it connects back to what I learned about governance on Day 2. Tone at the top matters. If leadership treats security as a compliance exercise, the rest of the organization will too. If leadership treats it as an ongoing operational responsibility — and backs that up with real attention and resources — the culture follows. That is a governance challenge as much as a technical one.

